    "explanation": "<p>The given analogy is Courage : Bravery ::</p>\n<p>Yearning : __________ .</p>\n<p>Understanding the Relationship :</p>\n<p>\"Courage\" and \"Bravery\" are synonymous; bravery is an expression or characteristic of courage.</p>\n<p>\"Yearning\" means a strong desire or deep longing for something.</p>\n<p>From option (A) :</p>\n<p>Longing : This is the correct answer because \"longing\" is synonymous with \"yearning.\"</p>\n<p>From option (B) :</p>\n<p>Yelling : This is incorrect because yelling is related to shouting, not yearning.</p>\n<p>From option (C) :</p>\n<p>Yawning : This is incorrect because yawning is an involuntary action related to tiredness or boredom, not desire.</p>\n<p>From option (D) :</p>\n<p>Glaring : This is incorrect because glaring means staring intensely, often angrily, which is unrelated to yearning.</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
